</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA83699025C4472FEFAFB66FC6FE12A" blockId="88.[313,1268,564,811]" box="[353,921,564,588]" pageId="88" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="B963EA8B025C4472FEFAFB66FE17E12A" box="[353,481,564,588]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="230">Etymology.</emphasis>
Gr. 
<emphasis id="B963EA8B025C4472FD81FB66FD99E12A" box="[538,623,564,588]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="230">brachýs</emphasis>
, ‘short’, 
<emphasis id="B963EA8B025C4472FD4CFB66FCD6E12D" box="[727,800,564,587]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="230">stigma</emphasis>
‘a brand’.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA83699025C4472FEFAFB06FD38E1CD" blockId="88.[313,1268,564,811]" pageId="88" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="B963EA8B025C4472FEFAFB06FE23E10D" box="[353,469,596,619]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="230">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Rather small species, with a very short stigma at the end of r1. Eyes separated. Antenna yellowish brown, third segment slightly deeper than long, with blunt apex. Legs and coxae yellow.
</paragraph>
